## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="a02b8-102">Esta extensão está presente apenas para serviços hospedados no IIS ou WAS.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a02b8-102">This extension is present only for services hosted in IIS or WAS.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a02b8-103">Services pode determinar se eles estão hospedados no IIS ou WAS, recuperando essa extensão de seus <xref:System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase>, conforme mostrado no exemplo a seguir.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a02b8-103">Services can determine whether they are hosted in IIS or WAS by retrieving this extension from their <xref:System.ServiceModel.ServiceHostBase>, as shown in the following example.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="a02b8-104">O exemplo a seguir mostra como recuperar o <xref:System.ServiceModel.Activation.VirtualPathExtension> do host de serviço e retornam um valor que está hospedado no IIS ou WAS.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a02b8-104">The following example shows how to recover the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Activation.VirtualPathExtension> from the service host and return a value that it is hosted in IIS or WAS.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
bool isHosted = false;  
ServiceHostBase host = OperationContext.Current.Host;  
VirtualPathExtension vpe = host.Extentions.Find<VirtualPathExtension>();  
  
if( vpe != null )  
Console.WriteLine("The virtualPath of the hosted Service is  {0}", vpe.VirtualPath);  
```
